claim.claim-text:
A method for use in a wireless transmit/receive unit, WTRU, the method comprising:
receiving a voice call service from an Internet Protocol, IP, multimedia subsystem, IMS, via a first radio access network, RAN;
establishing a connection to the IMS via a second RAN, wherein the second RAN is a cellular RAN;
initiating a handover of the voice call service from the first RAN to the second RAN; and
performing the handover while continuously receiving the voice call service from the IMS during the handover and maintaining a connection to the first RAN while simultaneously maintaining a connection to the cellular RAN.

A wireless transmit/receive unit, WTRU, comprising:
a dual-mode transceiver configured to:
receive a voice call service from an Internet Protocol, IP, multimedia subsystem, IMS, via a first radio access network, RAN;
establish a connection to the IMS via a second RAN, wherein the second RAN is a cellular RAN;
initiate a handover of the voice call service from the first RAN to the second RAN; and
perform the handover while continuously receiving the voice call service from the IMS during the handover and maintaining a connection to the first RAN while simultaneously maintaining a connection to the cellular RAN.
